“It is the BEST morning ever that I get to announce Harper is NED (no evidence of disease anywhere in her body)! It is an absolute miracle. Her tumor that is now just dead scar tissue was not supposed to shrink ever or much at all, it SHRUNK by 60%! 

Our journey is full of pain, growth, and happiness. I cannot begin to thank Candace Silvers enough for what she has done for Harper and myself. We would not be here it if were not for Candace and her tireless effort to get Harper NED and her behavior classes and academy for me. When we found Candace Harper was in very bad shape and the chemo was literally killing her and I was not in a good place mentally. 

The moment we started with Candace our lives changed and Harper was beginning to tolerate the chemo and actually start to live like a "normal" teenager. I was finding balance and strength in her modality and behavior work. She gave us both our lives back. 

I again cannot thank Candace enough for always being on call for us and loving Harper just the way she is (a tad sassy :). She has an incredible aptitude to connect with people, especially children and Harper became her biggest fan. When Harper was first in the hospital she would hide her healings for fear of what people would think. She eventually saw so many miracles she didn't care who watched and was telling everyone that would listen. As we were walking out of the hospital yesterday we saw a nurse we had often and we told her Harper was cancer free and the nurse said, "your energy lady did it!". We changed many people in that hospital to look further beyond what they know, especially the nurses and a couple doctors. 

Cancer is an ugly beast and we will forever be humbled by it. I will never stop fighting and praying for those who are still in the fight. Don't stop! Keep fighting, you got this! 

As for us, Candace will always be a staple for Harper. She gets scans every three months and we plan to keep the good news rolling. 

Thank you Candace and community. We love you beyond measure. I love this pic because this is how our lives are. Candace holding our Harper up.” -Niki Humpherys

“I have some beautiful news that I know you will be thrilled to hear.

Abigail had the results today about the nodules they took out of her lungs last month. Of the four nodules, three were not cancerous, one was, but it did not grow. The consultant cannot explain this and on top of this, they were able to take it out cleanly and with clear margins. 

As a result, where they had scheduled her for chemo up to October, she only needs one more round in July, because there is no evidence of disease!!!!!!!”
The presence of presence🌻

Eyal suffered from chronic eye inflammation for more than a year, caused by an unknown allergy. The left eyelid was constantly swollen and seemed almost half shut, with daily discharge, and he has experienced almost constant irritation and pain.

He was prescribed ointments and eye drops, with the doctors telling them that it will pass when he grows older.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

His first treatment with Candace was through a picture. A few days after that there was a visible improvement in his eye.

The next 4 treatments were via Zoom, for only 15 minutes for each treatment. About 3 weeks later, he woke up in the morning with his eye about 95% better than it was, no inflammation, no irritation and almost no swelling.

This incredible healing has stayed to this day, months after his first healing.

“Both of us cannot thank Ms. Silvers enough for ending a yearlong of suffering and worrying about it getting worse or his eye permanently damaged. It was incredible to witness a healing that works even from the other side of the world, is completely noninvasive, painless and without any drugs. We are truly grateful.” -Meital, Eyal’s mother
